         The revolving credit agreement is a $200 million facility providing
for revolving credit borrowing with interest at market or prime rates.  This
facility was amended during 1993 to permit the Company to extend its maturity
to December 31, 1995.  The facility is secured by the pledge of the common
stock of UC Lending and UC Life and a security interest in the Company's
intercompany receivable from UC Lending.  This debt facility is also guaranteed
by all subsidiaries of the Company except UG Title, UC Life and FMC.  The
Company is required under the agreement to maintain certain financial ratios
and meet certain net worth and indebtedness tests.  At December 31, 1993, $26.0
million of retained earnings were available for cash dividends.

         In addition to the above facilities, the Company has arrangements with
banks providing for short-term unsecured borrowings of up to $8.5 million, of
which $.5 million was outstanding at December 31, 1993.  Borrowings under
similar arrangements at December 31, 1992 were $1.1 million.  All of these
loans bear interest at market or prime rates.

         The long-term notes payable outstanding as of December 31, 1993
represents borrowings under the Company's revolving credit facility which
matures on December 31, 1995.

         The Company made payments for interest of $9.5 million, $13.2 million
and $18.4 million during the years ended December 31, 1993, 1992 and 1991,
respectively.





