6.       INCOME TAXES

         The Company implemented the provisions of SFAS 109, "Accounting for
Income Taxes," in the first quarter of 1993.  Under the provisions of SFAS 109,
deferred income taxes are recognized using the liability method whereby enacted
statutory rates are applied to cumulative temporary differences based on when
and how they are expected to affect the tax return.  Implementation of the
provisions of SFAS 109 did not have a material effect on previously reported
net income.  Adoption of SFAS 109 resulted in a $2.8 million increase in the
Company's deferred income tax liability and a $2.8 million decrease in retained
earnings at December 31, 1989. Prior year financial statements have been
restated accordingly.

